  "text": "Computerized cognitive training (CCT) ''is modestly effective at improving cognitive performance in healthy older adults'', find Michael Valenzuela and colleagues, who systematically review the evidence in this week's PLOS Medicine [CITATION_1] . This is a conclusion of value to academics in the field and to those with interest in selling training programmes. The value to others depends on how well they understand the conclusion's limits.",
